nd the volatile markets of more recent years. Katzenstein maintains that democratic corporatism is an effective way of coping with a rapidly changing world, a more effective way than the United States and several other large industrial countries have yet managed to discover.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIndustrial policyzEurope. 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  asocial corporatism, economic crisis of 1930 and 1940, world economies, west european politics and policies, western europe economics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170036140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501700361423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501700361/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles